#Dstv403​ #eNCA Editor's note: Watch Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga's briefing on #DStv403 and on eNCA.com on Sunday at 3pm. JOHANNESBURG - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga is set to brief the nation on Sunday as millions of children prepare to return to school on Monday. However, teacher unions say they remain concerned about safety amid the COVID-19 pandemic. Unions say they are most concerned about the Eastern Cape, KwaZulu-Natal, Limpopo and North West. The department says Sunday's briefing will address concerns raised by unions. Watch the video above for more details on this story. Good morning Mzansi! This is a reminder of the media briefing this afternoon at 15:00, on the @DBE_SA state of readiness for the opening of schools for 2021 @GovernmentZA @NationalCoGTA #BackToSchool #schoolsreopening pic.twitter.com/rjc9pNFBjs